What is an API?

An API (Application Programming Interface) acts like a waiter in a restaurant.

Customer

↓

Waiter (API)

↓

Kitchen (AI Model)

↓

Waiter

↓

Customer

The user never talks directly to the AI model; the API receives the request, sends it to the model, and returns the prediction.

Advantages of Deployment
------------------------

| Benefit           | Explanation                                        |
| ----------------- | -------------------------------------------------- |
| Global Access     | Users can access your app from anywhere.           |
| 24×7 Availability | The application can run continuously.              |
| Business Growth   | Enables companies to offer services online.        |
| Automation        | Reduces manual work.                               |
| Scalability       | Can support many users at once.                    |
| Collaboration     | Teams can use the same application.                |
| Monetization      | Can generate revenue through subscriptions or ads. |

========

Challenges

| Challenge       | Explanation                            |
| --------------- | -------------------------------------- |
| Server Downtime | Server becomes unavailable.            |
| High Traffic    | Many users may overload the system.    |
| Security        | Protecting user data and applications. |
| Cost            | Cloud resources may become expensive.  |
| Bugs            | Issues can appear in production.       |
| Updates         | New versions must be deployed safely.  |


=======

Local vs Cloud Deployment
------------------------

| Feature                 | Local | Cloud         |
| ----------------------- | ----- | ------------- |
| Accessible only to you  | ✅     | ❌             |
| Accessible worldwide    | ❌     | ✅             |
| Needs Internet          | ❌     | ✅ (for users) |
| Suitable for testing    | ✅     | ✅             |
| Suitable for production | ❌     | ✅             |


